Seven G3 rifles have been stolen after thugs raided Booker police post in Mumias, Kakamega county."The thugs raided the base at around midnight when an officer was on night patrol. They slashed and hit the officer on duty leaving him with wounds before the raiders escaped," the witness said."Another officer who was reporting for duty Wednesday morning found his colleague still unconscious" the witness said.A team of senior officers have visited the scene and rushed the injured officer to hospital as the hunt for the attackers is launched.This comes days after the government burnt 5,250 illicit small arms and light weapons in Ngong Hills, Kajiado.The government has been on the look out for people who carry illegal guns urging them to surrender the weapons to authorities.Members of the public were also asked to register their guns amid the government's effort to regulate the use of arms.